<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 10 at 5:52PM MDT  by NWS Saltlake</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Millard...eastern Beaver and northeastern Iron Counties through 630
PM MDT...
At 552 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles east of Milford, moving north at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Beaver, Milford, Minersville, Adamsville and Manderfield.
This includes the following highways...
Interstate 15 between mile markers 97 and 124.
Utah Route 21 between mile markers 71 and 107.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
